data.text:
"Paula is an original voice both in what she is saying and how she is saying it."

– Peter Gabriel

Pre-order a $39 food/beverage voucher for premium seating by calling 612-332-5299.

Paula Cole started as a jazz singer and now returns to pay homage to her first love of jazz and folk. Her single “Where Have All the Cowboys Gone?” reached the top ten of the Billboard Hot 100 in 1997, and the following year she won a Grammy Award for Best New Artist. Her song “I Don’t Want to Wait” was used as the theme song of the television show Dawson’s Creek.
